{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8f720907-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2281"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2281"},"text":"§ 2281.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" “Debt-for-nature exchange” defined","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purpose of this part, the term “debt-for-nature exchange” means the cancellation or redemption of the foreign debt of the government of a country in exchange for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8f720908-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2281/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that government’s making available local currencies (including through the issuance of bonds) which are used only for eligible projects involving the conservation or protection of the environment in that country (as described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2283"},"text":"section 2283 of this title","children":[],"tail":"); or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8f7451f9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2281/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that government’s financial resource or policy commitment to take certain specified actions to ensure the restoration, protection, or sustainable use of natural resources within that country; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8f7451fa-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2281/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a combination of assets and actions under both paragraphs (1) and (2).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8f7451fb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", pt. I, § 461 [471], as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/240/tVII/s711"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–240, title VII, § 711","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2521"},"text":"103 Stat. 2521","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8f7451fc-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8f7451fd-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8f7451fe-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2283"},"text":"Section 2283 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in par. (1), was in the original “section 463”, meaning "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195/s463"},"text":"section 463 of Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", which has been translated as meaning "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195/s463"},"text":"section 463 of Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":" relating to eligible projects rather than "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195/s463"},"text":"section 463 of Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", relating to the peace process in Central America, which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2273"